	(35553,'Introduction to Air Quality',158,4330,'Quantitative introduction to the engineering methods for the study of air quality. Topics include but are not limited to: estimation procedures for air pollution emissions; indoor air quality problems, impacts and control strategies; sources, impacts and control strategies for greenhouse gases; dispersion modeling for point sources; pollutant acidification of lakes; chemistry of stoichiometric and non-stoichiometric combustion; assessment methods for human exposure to air pollutants. Includes experimental analysis of air quality and air quality control processes, emphasizing experimental design, data evaluation, and report writing.',NULL,NULL,'spring',2015),
