	(35939,'Elements of Mechanical Design',143,4030,'Introduction to the design of mechanical components and integrated assemblies. Loads, stresses, and strains. Failure phenomena and material selection. Mechanical components including shafts, couplings, bearings, gears, springs, clutches, brakes, screws and fasteners, and bonded joints.',NULL,NULL,'spring',2015),
	(35940,'Computer Science Seminar',140,6900,'Presentation of current developments in computer science. Reports by students.',NULL,NULL,'spring',2015),
	(35941,'Lighting Technologies and Applications',139,4770,'This course provides students with an in-depth understanding of the components of advanced lighting systems and enables them to critically explore applications of those components. Through lectures, readings, assignments, and application projects, students acquire working knowledge of the relevant products and techniques for lighting application and develop solutions to lighting problems. Students will undertake practical applications of advanced lighting technologies and develop skills in the application of photometric data, use of manual and computer-based lighting calculations, and the development of lighting specifications.',NULL,NULL,'spring',2015),
