	(36150,'Investments I',160,6410,'The objectives of this course are: 1) to introduce the student to the most important investment instruments currently traded in U.S. financial markets, including forward and futures contracts, options, futures options and swaps on a variety of underlying instruments including fixed income securities; 2) to discuss the major distributions of modern financial economics in pricing them; 3) to discuss their uses by the investment community in practical investment strategies.',NULL,NULL,'spring',2015),
