	(36189,'Masterâ??s Thesis',158,6990,'Active participation in research, under the supervision of a faculty adviser, leading to a master?s thesis. Grades of S or U are assigned by the adviser each term to reflect the  student?s research progress for the given semester. Once the thesis has  been presentend, approved by the adviser, and accepted by the Office of  Graduate Education, it will be archived in a standard format in the  library.',NULL,NULL,'spring',2015),
