	(36702,'International Project Management',160,4390,'This course presents the concepts, techniques, and tools for managing global projects. The role of the project manager is examined, together with techniques for controlling cost, schedules and performance parameters. Course deliverables are designed to develop fundamental skills needed by project managers in today?s global competitive business environment. Topics include project leadership, project lifecycle methodology, business process development, benchmarking, project planning, execution and control, procurement, communications, organizational change, customer acceptance, performance metrics and project closure. This course is communication intensive.',NULL,NULL,'spring',2015),
